article.headline: UNC Greensboro 69, Furman 54
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Ricky Hickman came off the bench to score 31 points while Kyle Hines had a double-double with 24 points and 10 rebounds as UNC Greensboro defeated Furman 69-54 on Saturday. Ben Stywall added 10 rebounds for the Spartans (11-9, 8-2 SoCon), who scored 23 points off 16 Furman turnovers. Gerad Punch scored 12 points to lead the Paladins (10-11, 4-6), who shot just 12.5 percent from 3-point range (2-for-16). Robby Bostain added 10 points. The Spartans jumped out to a 20-4 lead in the first nine minutes of the game and led 33-22 at the half. Furman cut the lead to five, 48-43, midway through the second half. But Hickman scored 17 straight points to make it 65-47 with less than four minutes left to secure the win.
